main event: An unidentified object was observed descending at a slight angle before disappearing into clouds in Litchfield, Nebraska on October 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object was olive green and the size of a wash tub with tapered ends., The sighting lasted approximately 3-5 minutes., The observer did not report the sighting to anyone officially., Atmospheric conditions may have distorted the object's appearance., The conclusion of the observation was a balloon sighting.
sighted object: an olive green object the size of a wash tub
witness description: A 59-year-old female resident of Litchfield, Nebraska.
